<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900723-0033</DOCNO><DOCID>900723-0033.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Rio Algom Ltd.:   Closing of 2 Mines to Begin   As Early as September</HL><DATE>07/23/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B5</SO><CO>   ROM T.ROM RTZ</CO><LP>   Rio Algom Ltd. said it plans to close two of its uraniummines at the beginning of September, as much as nine monthssooner than the Toronto mining company had indicated.   Rio Algom, which is 52%-owned by RTZ Corp. of Britain,said the closures of the Quirke and Panel mines in ElliotLake, Ontario, will eliminate about 1,700 of the company'swork force of 5,000. A third mine in the area will continueto produce uranium under a long-term contract withprovincially owned Ontario Hydro.</LP><TEXT>   Rio Algom had said in January it planned to shut the twomines in the first half of 1991 because of low ore grades anddepressed uranium market prices. A Rio Algom spokesman saidthe closure date was advanced after agreements were reachedwith customers to reduce the amount of uranium contracted.</TEXT></DOC>